cription","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add 50 ng\/ml PMA and 1 mcg\/ml Ionomycin to wells B1-B7<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Add 0.05 mcg\/ml LPS to well C1<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Add 10 mcg\/ml Brefeldin A to wells A1-A3 and A6, B1-B3 and B6, C1, D2, D3, and D6. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":808098,"guid":"5E97A3F0CCF911E988A351B32AD37897","previous_id":808088,"previous_guid":"DAAAD280CCF611E988A351B32AD37897","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"040F4B1CFFB543D08CA0AAF61813EF03","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"04A25F33C6B443C9B420089031D7308B","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Prepare antibody panels for cell surface staining and made up to 50mcls PBA per sample.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Prepare antibody panels were for intracellular staining and make up to 50mcl with 0.2% saponin (in PBA buffer) for IL12, IL23, IL17A and IFN\u03b3 per sample. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Antibody panels for intracellular staining of ROR\u03b3(t) and T-Bet are made up to 50mcl with Permeabilization Buffer (Miltenyi FoxP3 Staining Buffer Set)<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":808099,"guid":"37D00220CCFA11E988A351B32AD37897","previous_id":808098,"previous_guid":"5E97A3F0CCF911E988A351B32AD37897","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"EC56B0301AD64A17A7A2D10B07AE44C6","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"A342734EB64B49E992EE3CE928DCCD50","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Transfer PBMCs to flow cytometry tubes after mixing well in wells and avoiding bubbles.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Add 1ml PBS.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Centrifuge at 1500RPM for 5 minutes.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Resuspend in dead cell stain and vortex. Incubate for 15 minutes at room temperature in dark. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">,<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":808100,"guid":"03D10B80CCFB11E988A351B32AD37897","previous_id":808099,"previous_guid":"37D00220CCFA11E988A351B32AD37897","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"79A0DA10904E4486B81F39ACA83751E7","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"0298BEEEE0AB4B239A2A4A496031DFC3","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add 1ml  PBA, vortex, and centrifuge as per step 7.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":808101,"guid":"235D5E90CCFB11E988A351B32AD37897","previous_id":808100,"previous_guid":"03D10B80CCFB11E988A351B32AD37897","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"A861F107A24E427180E76046910F6EF2","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"15ABCF608A7D4A31B1E07276CDC2EDD5","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add antibody cocktail, vortex, incubate for 15 minutes in the dark.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Then add 1ml PBA, vortex, and then centrifuge as per step 7. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":808102,"guid":"641D4C10CCFB11E988A351B32AD37897","previous_id":808101,"previous_guid":"235D5E90CCFB11E988A351B32AD37897","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"F13E778082B14EFEB88099426033C760","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"3A9E71BA7C984C6CBC97A2DFC6C47317","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Fix cells and permeabilise for intracellular staining as follows<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":808103,"guid":"74D11D70CCFB11E988A351B32AD37897","previous_id":808102,"previous_guid":"641D4C10CCFB11E988A351B32AD37897","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"41A9D5DD5811461DABCF85E32CD954B0","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"8F28E46C4D584B779FCBF70782348CA5","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">For wells 1,2,3, and 6 for A,B,C, and D:<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Fix with 0.5mls 4% PFA per tube and incubate for 10 minutes in the dark.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Add 1ml PBA, vortex, and then centrifuge as per step 7. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Permeabilise with 1ml 0.2% Saponin in dark for 10 minutes. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Centrifuge as per step 7. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Add intracellular antibody cocktails, vortex, and incubate for 20 minutes in the dark.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Add 1ml PBA, vortex, and centrifuge as per step 7. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Resuspend in 1% PFA 0.5mls for 10 minutes in the dark.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Add 1ml PBA, vortex, and centrifuge as per step 7. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Top up with few drops of PBA. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Store in fridge while acquiring with flow cytometer. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":808104,"guid":"307946B0CCFC11E988A351B32AD37897","previous_id":808103,"previous_guid":"74D11D70CCFB11E988A351B32AD37897","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"ADE31637616F44DEB357BE44D734BE53","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"58EF2CD06E39431EB3F144E98F2F4D4D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">For wells 4,5,and 7 for A,B,C, and D:<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Add 1ml Fixation.Permeabilisation Solution.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Incubate for 30 minutes in the dark.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Add 1ml PBA, vortex, and centrifuge as per step 7.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Add 1ml Permeabilisation Buffer, vortex, and centrifuge as per step 7.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Add intracellular antibody cocktail, vortex, and incubate for 30 minutes in the dark in the fridge.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Add 1ml cold permeabilisation buffer and centrifuge as per step 7. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Resuspend in 1% PFA, vortex, and incubate in the dark for 10 minutes. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Add 1ml PBA, vortex, and centrifuge as per step 7. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Top up with few drops of PBA. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Store in fridge while acquiring with flow cyometer. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":null,"materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Stimulation of PBMCs to study TH1 and TH17 Lymphocytes.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">PBMCs were incubated in medium alone, or stimulated for 5 hours with functional mAbs specific for CD3 and CD28, 0.05 \u03bcg\/ml lipopolysaccharide (LPS), or 50 ng\/ml phorbol myristate acetate (PMA) and 1 \u03bcg\/ml ionomycin. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Wells intended for intracellular staining for IL-23, IL-12, IL-17A, and IFN-\u03b3 were stimulated in the presence of brefeldin A to prevent cytokine release from the cells. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Antibody panels with 0.2% saponin were used for intracellular staining of IL12, IL23, IL17A and IFN\u03b3.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Antibody panels with Permeabilization Buffer (Miltenyi FoxP3 Staining Buffer Set) were made for intracellular staining of ROR\u03b3(t) and T-Bet.<\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1572365164}